  <releases>
    <release version="2.alpha" date="2022-10-23">
      <description>
        <ul>
          <li>Added power settings</li>
          <li>Added options to import/export settings in the global menu</li>
          <li>Added an option to enlarge welcome message</li>
          <li>Turned main window adaptive</li>
          <li>Turned pop-up dialogs adaptive</li>
          <li>Updated "about" window to the new style</li>
          <li>Improved style of welcome message input field</li>
          <li>Renamed sidebar section "Miscellaneous" to "Login Screen"</li>
          <li>Renamed global menu option "Import user settings" to "Load session settings"</li>
          <li>The app, now, shows an error notification when trying to apply settings if logo
              is enabled and the chosen logo image does not exist on the system anymore</li>
          <li>Colored commandline output</li>
          <li>Fixed "Apply Current Display Settings" feature not working on Ubuntu and Ubuntu-like systems</li>
          <li>Fixed some text showing up untranslated even if translation existed</li>
          <li>Fixed some typos</li>
          <!--
          <li>Improved support for multiple installations of the app on the same system</li>
          -->
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="1.1" date="2022-10-8">
      <description>
        <ul>
          <li>Fixed: Cannot apply settings anymore</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Note: You may need to reinstall GNOME Shell in order for 'Apply' button to start working again.
        </p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="1.0" date="2022-09-23">
      <description>
        <p>
          Warning: You will lose some settings after updating from v0.6 or any earlier version to this or any later version.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Added support for incomplete shell themes</li>
          <li>Fixed: Cannot change login screen logo from Flatpak version of the app</li>
          <li>Prevent app launch when argument provided to `--verbosity` option is invalid</li>
          <li>Updated the info shown on app's software-store page</li>
          <li>New App Icon that follows GNOME HIG</li>
          <li>Only one instance of the app can be open at a time</li>
          <li>When applying settings, the app does not freeze anymore</li>
          <li>The app shows a "Log Out" dialog right after settings are applied</li>
          <li>Added new dialogs to show errors to the user instead of panicking on the terminal</li>
          <li>When applying current display settings, scaling is also applied (may not work on all systems)</li>
          <li>The app is now DBusActivatable</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
  </releases>

